# Documentation sync on fundamental changes

When you change something **fundamental**, update the relevant documentation **in the same task** before finishing. Do not leave READMEs, Cursor rules, or examples pointing at removed commands or old behavior.

## What counts as fundamental

- **Scripts:** `pnpm dev`, `build`, `lint`, `preview`, `test`, `test:pr`, `test:coverage`
- **Data model:** Dexie schema, types in `src/models/types.ts`, migrations, seed data shape
- **Features:** new views, export/import format (`ExportData` version), routing, drag-and-drop behavior
- **Stack:** dependencies, build config (`vite.config.ts`, `vitest.config.ts`), path aliases
- **Styling:** Tailwind theme tokens, shadcn/ui primitives, styling conventions — see **`projocalypse-tailwind-shadcn.mdc`**
- **Cursor rules/skills:** new or renamed `.cursor/rules/*.mdc`, `.cursor/skills/*`, slash commands
- **Product / UX:** keyboard shortcuts, backup filename pattern, IndexedDB database name

Cosmetic refactors, test-only changes, and internal renames with no user-visible effect are **not** fundamental unless docs already name the old symbol.

## Where to update (use what applies)

| Change type | Update at minimum |
|-------------|-------------------|
| Run commands / setup / tests | [README.md](../../README.md) |
| Data model / IndexedDB | README + inline comments in `src/db/schema.ts` if non-obvious |
| Export/import format | README (backup pattern, version) + validation in `src/lib/export-import.ts` |
| Styling / UI stack | README tech stack; **`projocalypse-tailwind-shadcn.mdc`** if conventions shift |
| Cursor rules/skills | [.cursor/README.md](../README.md) — `projocalypse-<topic>.mdc` / `projocalypse-<topic>/` per **`projocalypse-filenames.mdc`** |
| Ship / test workflow | **`projocalypse-feature-ship.mdc`**, **`projocalypse-tests.mdc`**, **`projocalypse-pr-loop`** skill if gates change |
| Future planning docs | `doc/PLAN/*.md` when a `doc/` tree exists — layout per **`projocalypse-docs.mdc`** |

Terminology and CAPITALIZED paths under `doc/`: follow **`projocalypse-docs.mdc`**.

## Quality bar

- Replace **stale commands** (e.g. `npm run`, removed scripts) wherever they appear in docs you touch.
- Prefer linking to **[README.md](../../README.md)** for local workflow instead of duplicating long command tables in many files.
- Keep edits **scoped** to what changed; no unrelated doc drive-bys.
- When adding a feature listed in README, ensure README still accurately describes it after your change.

## Done checklist (mental)

Fundamental change landed → README updated → Cursor `.cursor/README.md` if rules/skills changed → export/schema comments if data shape changed → related rule files if conventions shifted.
